cs.SC, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.NA, cs.CA. 

The paper deals with the computation of difference Groebner bases, which is a topic in symbolic computation and algebraic geometry. Therefore, cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the implementation of the algorithm in Maple, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The applications of the algorithm to finite difference approximations and Feynman integrals suggest that cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.CA (Computational Geometry) are also possible sub-categories.
